Well, I've never been into furry for the community. Mostly because by the time I learned what furry was it was 90% circlejerking by people with money to burn keeping artists busy churning out more pics of their characters. I wanted no part of that.

Furry has just about always been another color of sprinkles on sex icecream to me. Just a fetish.

Now, am I aware of the difference between then and now? Most definitely. I have a habit of doing internet archeology about shit and there is a definite schism between what's being done now and say, what was being done when Schwartz first launched Sabrina Online. Plus, some of the oldest examples of fur shit I've seen (that isn't LMAO WALL PAINTINGS) is some sci-fi where furries were entire different species and they wanted nothing to do with humans. The entirety of the books were all about exploring the culture of this species of space cats and other ayys while the single human was used as the eye and mouth piece for the audience going 'man, this is some weird shit, you guys.' when appropriate.

Am I upset about the fact that I missed the furry community when the height of comedy was 'haha dogs pee to mark their territory look how animal like they are?' Not in the slightest. Do I feel as if I'm missing something because I don't care about the logistics of making shoes for digitigrade anthros? Not really.

Honestly it just feels like this post is going "Once upon a time, we were sci-fi/fantasy enthusiasts with a niche, and now it's just a boring circlejerk." At the same time, I don't see 'ye olden days of the beast people clans' as something to put on a pedestal. It's just the changing of the times, not a coup.

Special snowflake faggots have always existed, too, by the way. Unless everyone finally forgot Chakats were a thing.
